-- Ecuador’s Lafarge Cementos Announces $36 Million Cash Dividend
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2012-04-02T17:45:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/ecuador-s-lafarge-cementos-announces-36-million-cash-dividend.html
Shareholders of Lafarge Cementos SA,
an Ecuadorean cement producer, approved a $36 million cash
dividend for the 2011 earnings period.  Quito-based Lafarge, a unit of the world’s biggest cement
maker,  Lafarge SA (LF) , will distribute the payment to shareholders
this month, according to a statement published today on the
Guayaquil securities exchange’s website. The company didn’t give
the per share amount.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nathan Gill in Quito at 
 ngill4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 Papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  